\"image_resized\" style=\"width:381.5px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Edge of Card standing up on table\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:381.5px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Heatpipes and Heatplate and Heatsink\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/13-2.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"></p><p>The GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC uses GIGABYTE’s WINDFORCE 3X Cooling System with alternate spinning fans.&nbsp; This system features 2x 90mm and 1x80mm unique blade fans.&nbsp; The airflow is split by a triangular fan edge and guided through the 3D stripe curve on the fan surface.&nbsp; Graphene nano lubricant is used to extend the life of sleeve-bearing fans by 2.1 times and is quieter.&nbsp; The blade fans alternate spinning.&nbsp; Alternate spinning fans can reduce turbulence of adjacent fans and increase air pressure.&nbsp; GIGABYTE uses GPU 3D active fan to provide semi-passive cooling, and the fans will remain off when the GPU is in low load or power.&nbsp;<br><br>The cooling system also uses 7 composite copper heat pipes and a large copper plate with direct contact with the GPU and VRAM for high-efficiency heat dissipation.&nbsp; The large copper plate combines the composite heat pipes to transfer heat generated from the interior cores to the heat sink.&nbsp; This video card uses GIGABYTE Screen Cooling which is an extended heatsink design that allows airflow to pass through the video card providing better heat dissipation.&nbsp; There is a full metal backplate for protection.&nbsp; It enhances the structure of the video card.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:182.25px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Dual BIOS Switch\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/14-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:182.25px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Label\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/15.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:182.25px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Screen Cooling\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/16.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:182.25px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC Shining Light Through Screen Cooling\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"></p><p>GIGABYTE has put a DUAL BIOS on this video card.&nbsp; There is a DUAL BIOS switch that switches from OC mode to Silent mode.&nbsp; The default mode is OC mode for full performance out of the box.&nbsp; This video card is built with extreme durability and overclocking ability.&nbsp; It uses a better power phase design to allow MOSFETs to operate at lower temperatures and over-temperature protection and load balancing for each MOSFET.&nbsp; It uses Ultra Durable certified chokes and capacitors.&nbsp; It has a friendly PCB design using a fully automated production process to ensure top-quality circuit boards and eliminate sharp protrusions.&nbsp; This video card requires 2x 8-pin power connectors.&nbsp; Recommended PSU is 750W.</p><p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:248.672px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC I/O Ports\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-768x432.jpg 768w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-1200x675.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19-1568x882.jpg 1568w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/19.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"100vw\" width=\"1024\"><img class=\"image_resized\" style=\"width:248.672px;\" src=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/20-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 3090 GAMING OC GIGABYTE Logo RGB Lit Up\" srcset=\"https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/20-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/20-300x169.jpg 300w, https://cdn.thefpsreview.com/w